AN ABSA bank employee in Elim, Limpopo has been bust by the Hawks for a multi-million rand fraud. The 27-year-old ABSA bank consultant allegedly stole R25 million from the Limpopo Provincial Government account and deposited it into different accounts that he had opened. Hawks spokesman Captain Matimba Maluleke says despite all the secret efforts by the suspect, the team of investigators attentively managed to trace and freeze the complex web of the bank accounts linked to him. "The suspect was arrested at his workplace in Elim town on Friday and his house was searched whereby four Absa ATM cards, two withdrawal slips and R2030 hard cash were found and seized." "While our investigations are underway in this matter, more people are expected to be arrested." He said. Matimba also confirmed that the arrested suspect will make his first court appearance in the Waterval Magistrateâ€™s Court tomorrow (Monday, 20 July 2020) facing fraud charges.